Here's an example of how to create a simple search bar using PHP, HTML, and CSS.

**search.php**
```php
<?php
// connect to database (e.g. MySQL)
$db = new mysqli("localhost", "username", "password", "database");

// check connection
if ($db->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $db->connect_error);
}

// get search query from form submission
if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    $search_query = $_POST['search'];

    // sanitize user input (e.g. escape special characters)
    $search_query = mysqli_real_escape_string($db, $search_query);

    // query database for results
    $query = "SELECT * FROM table_name WHERE column_name LIKE '%$search_query%'";
    $result = $db->query($query);

    // display search results
    if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
        while ($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
            echo "<p>" . $row['column_name'] . "</p>";
        }
    } else {
        echo "No results found.";
    }
} else {
    ?>
    <form action="<?php echo $_SERVER["PHP_SELF"]; ?>" method="post">
        <input type="search" name="search" placeholder="Search...">
        <button type="submit">Search</button>
    </form>
    <?php
}
?>
```
**index.html**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Search Bar</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <?php include 'search.php'; ?>
</body>
</html>
```
**style.css**
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

form {
    width: 50%;
    margin: 40px auto;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

input[type="search"] {
    width: 80%;
    height: 40px;
    padding: 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

button[type="submit"] {
    width: 20%;
    height: 40px;
    padding: 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: #fff;
    cursor: pointer;
}

button[type="submit"]:hover {
    background-color: #3e8e41;
}
```
This example creates a basic search bar with a form that submits to itself. When the user types something in the input field and clicks the submit button, the PHP code searches for results in the database based on the query.

Please note:

* This is a simplified example and you should adjust it according to your specific needs (e.g., table/column names).
* This code uses `mysqli` extension for database connectivity. Consider using `PDO` or other more secure alternatives.
* This example doesn't handle pagination, sorting, or other advanced features that might be required in a real-world application.

Remember to replace the placeholders with actual values (database connection credentials, table and column names) in your code.

